# Markdown Block Formatting

This rule establishes standards for Markdown content blocks in the presentation to ensure consistency and readability.

## Basic Block Types

### Headers
Use consistent header levels with proper hierarchy:
```markdown
# Main Title (H1) - Use only once per slide
## Section Title (H2)
### Subsection (H3)
#### Detail Point (H4)
```

### Lists
Use consistent list formatting:
```markdown
* Unordered list item
* Another item
  * Nested item with proper indentation (2 spaces)
  * Another nested item
    * Further nesting

1. Ordered list item
2. Second item
   1. Nested ordered item
   2. Another nested item
```

### Blockquotes
Format quotes consistently:
```markdown
> This is a quote from an important source
> 
> Multiple paragraphs in a blockquote require the > symbol on blank lines
>
> <cite>â€” Attribution</cite>
```

### Code Blocks
For inline code:
```markdown
Use `backticks` for inline code elements
```

For code blocks:
```markdown
```javascript
// Code block with language specification
function example() {
  return "Hello world";
}
```
```

## Advanced Formatting

### Tables
Format tables consistently:
```markdown
| Header 1 | Header 2 | Header 3 |
|----------|----------|----------|
| Cell 1   | Cell 2   | Cell 3   |
| Cell 4   | Cell 5   | Cell 6   |
```

### Definition Lists
Use this format for definition lists:
```markdown
<dl>
  <dt>Term</dt>
  <dd>Definition of the term</dd>
  
  <dt>Another Term</dt>
  <dd>Definition of another term</dd>
</dl>
```

### Footnotes
Use consistent footnote formatting:
```markdown
This statement requires citation[^1].

[^1]: This is the footnote content.
```

## RevealJS-Specific Markdown

### Slide Separators
Use consistent slide separators:
```markdown
# Slide 1

Content for slide 1

---

# Slide 2

Content for slide 2

---

# Slide 3

Content for slide 3
```

### Fragments
Format fragment reveals consistently:
```markdown
* Regular item
* Item revealed second <!-- .element: class="fragment" -->
* Item revealed third <!-- .element: class="fragment" -->
* Item revealed fourth <!-- .element: class="fragment highlight-blue" -->
```

### Speaker Notes
Format speaker notes consistently:
```markdown
# Slide Title

Content visible to audience

Note:
Speaker notes go here.
Multiple lines are supported.
These are only visible in presenter view.
```

### Columns
Format multi-column content consistently:
```markdown
<div class="two-columns">
  <div class="column">
    
## First Column
* Point 1
* Point 2
    
  </div>
  <div class="column">
    
## Second Column
* Point A
* Point B
    
  </div>
</div>
```

## Custom Elements

### Info Boxes
Format information boxes consistently:
```markdown
<div class="info-box">
  <h3>Important Information</h3>
  <p>Critical details that need highlighting.</p>
</div>
```

### Warning Boxes
Format warning boxes consistently:
```markdown
<div class="warning-box">
  <h3>Warning</h3>
  <p>Critical warning or caution notice.</p>
</div>
```

### Tip Boxes
Format tip boxes consistently:
```markdown
<div class="tip-box">
  <h3>Pro Tip</h3>
  <p>Helpful advice or shortcut information.</p>
</div>
```

By following these formatting standards, Markdown content will remain consistent and professional throughout the presentation.
